                    "comment": "jorisvandenbossche opened a new pull request, #14516:\nURL: https://github.com/apache/arrow/pull/14516\n\n   Dataset scanning was using the C++ default memory backend, and not the one set from python (if not specified explicitly). `maybe_unbox_memory_pool(memory_pool)` is meant to always be called (not only if `memory_pool is not None`), since this will then return the python default memory pool if `memory_pool` is not specified. \n\n\n",
